# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

## [0.0.3] - 2026-07-04

### Added
- # and ## to report runtime errors
- const support
- added library functions print, println, println_debug, pop_count, load_text_file, save_text_file
- added library functions char_to_int, int_to_char

### Changed
- Renumbered phases in README. Current phase is now 0
- count_trailing_zeros is a proper function rather than operator
- support for char-char (returns int)

### Fixed
- Fixed arg checking on library functions
- Now Display the line numbers in parser errors
- Various other error message improvements

## [0.0.2] - 2026-07-02

### Added
- String and char support
- tests/roman_numerals.rw to demonstrate char and string support

### Fixed
- Segmentation fault when a function in the command line calling expression did not exist

## [0.0.1] - 2026-07-01 — Initial release

### Added
- Types: integer, boolean, list
- Pattern matching with guards
- List construction and splat operators
- Tail-call elimination
- Built-in arithmetic, logical, bitwise, and shift operators
- `count_trailing_zeros` operator
- CLI interface for running ReWrite programs
- Example programs: factorial, listn, nprime, nqueens (two versions)
